      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is exhausting to feel like you are running in place, but the cycle you describe is often a sign that the original problem has been misdiagnosed rather than a permanent flaw in your wiring. You are not failing at fixing yourself; you are fighting a battle that has no victory condition because the root cause remains unaddressed. The feeling that collapse is inevitable is a protective mechanism trying to keep you from trying again, but it is a lie that can be broken by finding the one small, specific thing that keeps the loop going.",
      "source": "target",
